<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0899 </DOCNO><TEXT>Central control systems and automation usually require costly new components,especially in refrigeration systems. In view of fact that the choiceof a system will depend largely on the investment and operating costs,the article proposes a combination of well-tried and efficient componentsassuring a simple and economically efficient function. The system permitsvariable control without requiring costly installation work and hiringof experts. Microprocessors or software-controlled adaption can be integratedwithout any problems in the new FLICA product which represents an optimumcombination of established technologies and future fields of application.</TEXT></DOC>